OL,4,Ccalling for reform of a crucial care
OL,5,Coption
OL,7,FFor Tracey's 22-year-old daughter
OL,8,FEllie, she was someone who needed
OL,9,Fround the clock care. Tracey gave up
OL,10,Fher job as a teacher and along with
OL,11,FEllie's younger sister Kayla, they
OL,12,Fmanaged most of the time.
OL,14,FEllie often wakes several times a
OL,15,Fnight and cannot even turn without
OL,16,Fsomeone helping. For Tracey and Kayla
OL,17,Fthat means sleepless nights.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G4/16
