OL,3,CUp Close examines why families are
OL,4,Ccalling for reform of a crucial care
OL,5,Coption
OL,7,FThe only respite Tracey had been
OL,8,Freceiving was through a Direct Care
OL,9,Fpackage which was agreed with the
OL,10,FNorthern Trust in 2022 which meant a
OL,11,Fcarer could come in and give Tracey a
OL,12,Fchance to eat, sleep, take a break.
OL,14,FSo for Tracey to be told that her
OL,15,Fcarers could no longer carry out
OL,16,Fhealthcare tasks was devastating. With
OL,17,Fthe level of care that Ellie needed,
OL,18,Fit meant that Tracey was the only one
OL,19,Fwho could manage Ellie's peg tube so
OL,20,Feffectively the little respite she
OL,21,Fgot....was gone.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G5/16
