OL,7,FDue to the limit on DP carers
OL,8,Fundertaking health care tasks, we
OL,9,Fwitness how she has to clock off as a
OL,10,Fcarer to administer Lee's insulin.
OL,12,FShe is back in mum mode and then
OL,13,Fclocks on as his carer again once
OL,14,Fshe's finished.
OL,16,FShe says the problem lies with
OL,17,Fdecision makers who don't know what
OL,18,Flife is like as a carer and what that
OL,19,Fentails. She says accessing services
OL,20,Fis a constant battle and when one
OL,21,Fends, another begins.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G10/16
